<section xml:id="wec-configure" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <title>Configure &wec;</title>
    <formalpara>
        <title>Purpose:</title>
        <para/>
    </formalpara>
    <para>Once you have configured your event source computer(s), the next step is to configure your event collector, in this case, the &wec; for &abbrev;. </para>
    <note>
        <para>The configuration file of &wecabbrev; is YAML based. Note that YAML uses spaces, not tabs, for indentation.</para>
    </note>
    <para>To configure &wecabbrev;, use the following options.</para>
    <para>For an example <filename>wec.yaml</filename> file, see <xref linkend="wec-config-example"/>.</para>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="simplesect-server.xml"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="simplesect-port.xml"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="simplesect-keyfile.xml"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="simplesect-certfile.xml"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="option-cadir.xml"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="simplesect-log.xml"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="simplesect-eventdestination.xml"/>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="simplesect-subscriptions.xml"/>
</section>
